</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1692,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
- Coxa I brown to black; face and frons covered with brownish pruinosity (as in 
<figureCitation box="[976,1033,1903,1924]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1038,1061]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,555,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1247,555,1017]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Photographs of male heads, anterior view. 5. Hurleyella belizensis sp. nov.; 6. Hurleyella salina sp. nov. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601776/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); wing with M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1175,1182,1916,1928]" fontSize="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">1</subScript>
slightly arching anteriorly only near apex (
<figureCitation box="[380,439,1934,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1164,1187]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,195,1142]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[340,1247,193,1143]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Photographs of male wings. 3. Hurleyella belizensis sp. nov.; 4. Hurleyella salina sp. nov. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601774/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Runyon, J. B. &amp; Robinson, H." box="[450,705,1934,1955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="57 - 65" refId="ref7031" refString="Runyon, J. B. &amp; Robinson, H. (2010) Hurleyella, a new genus of Nearctic Dolichopodidae (Diptera). Zootaxa, 2400, 57 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2400.1.6" type="journal article" year="2010">Runyon &amp; Robinson 2010</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3); halter brown; hypandrium asymmetrical (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1239,1323,1934,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1902,1925]" captionTargetBox="[176,1360,242,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1408,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Hurleyella belizensis sp. nov., male terminalia. 7. ventral view; 8. left lateral view. Abbreviations: epandepandrium; epd lobe—epandrial lobe; fsur—lateroapical flange of surstylus; hyprct—hypoproct; left hypd lobe—left lobe of hypandrium; right hypd lobe—right lobe of hypandrium; sbepand scl—subepandrial sclerite; S—abdominal sternite; Tabdominal tergite. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601778/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
), not hoodlike; habitat not noticeably alkaline....................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="551" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1692,2014]" box="[151,1436,1993,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1993,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
3 Surstylus apically with large membranous flange (
<bibRefCitation author="Runyon, J. B. &amp; Robinson, H." box="[706,1022,1993,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="57 - 65" refId="ref7031" refString="Runyon, J. B. &amp; Robinson, H. (2010) Hurleyella, a new genus of Nearctic Dolichopodidae (Diptera). Zootaxa, 2400, 57 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2400.1.6" type="journal article" year="2010">Runyon &amp; Robinson 2010, fig. 5</bibRefCitation>
) (Nearctic)........................ 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,290]" box="[151,1436,151,173]" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,151,173]" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">
- Surstylus with very small, inconspicuous membranous flange (
<figureCitation box="[826,912,151,172]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1902,1925]" captionTargetBox="[176,1360,242,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1408,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Hurleyella belizensis sp. nov., male terminalia. 7. ventral view; 8. left lateral view. Abbreviations: epandepandrium; epd lobe—epandrial lobe; fsur—lateroapical flange of surstylus; hyprct—hypoproct; left hypd lobe—left lobe of hypandrium; right hypd lobe—right lobe of hypandrium; sbepand scl—subepandrial sclerite; S—abdominal sternite; Tabdominal tergite. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601778/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
, fsur) (
<collectingCountry box="[981,1045,151,172]" name="Belize" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Belize</collectingCountry>
).............. 
